<br>
It is WAR...people die in wars.  There are no fucking NPC's or PC's that your attacks magically have no effect on in the real world, bucko.  Bullets don't care what they hit, the only ruleset they follow is the Laws of Physics.  That's the real world, maybe you should experience some of it.<br>
<br>
You say they were unarmed.  Bullshit.  Somebody was behind the wheel and refused to stop as per POSTED WARNINGS stating that lethal force might be used if the warnings were ignored.  Warning shots were fired, and a 1000 pound MISSLE was still barreling down at soldiers with guns.  It didn't have any explosives, true...but try telling the 14 soldiers who were injured by that Egyptian truckdriver that their injuries were not caused by someone who turned a vehicle into a weapon.<br>
<br>
Apparently, you are also forgetting that Saddam has deliberately starved his people for much of this war...not to mention the decades of atrocities he has committed.  But, I guess since Saddam is the underdog here, you can easily put that out of your mind.  By your thinking, I guess Ed Bundy was an underdog too, and the US is totally evil since we were so much more powerful and we executed a mass murderer....oooh, bad bad Americans!<br>
<br>
Who can know the truth about why it happened?  Certainly not you or me, we were not there.  It may have been the result of the driver panicking, that I will not deny.  However, Pedi had it right...Considereing the amount of firepower around a checkpoint, common sense says you won't outrun it.  So, if warning shots were fired, I would have stopped...wouldn't you?<br>
<br>
However, given Saddam's history and his current strategies in this war, I would not put it past him or his regime to have put kids into a vehicle and told the driver to go out and become a martyr.<br>
